11/01/2005
ATHENS, Greece -- The new US Ambassador to Greece, Charles Ries, has officially assumed his duties, according to media reports in Athens on Monday (10 January).
Ries, appointed last month, succeeds Thomas Miller.
In other news Monday, the Greek government said it would clamp down on sports-related hooliganism following an outbreak of violence during a first division football game.
About 600 fans invaded the pitch Sunday at a stadium in Athens, fighting each other and the police.
One man was reported in serious condition and dozens of others required treatment.
(MPA, AFP - 10/01/05)
